<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a57f62c-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s6313"><num value="6313">§ 6313.</num><heading> Relationship with State law</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall prohibit a State from adopting or enforcing supplemental or more stringent laws or regulations not inconsistent with this chapter, or criminal, civil, or administrative fines for violations of such laws or regulations.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a57f62d-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/104/272/s22">Pub. L. 104–272, § 22</ref>, formerly § 14, <date date="1996-10-09">Oct. 9, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3313">110 Stat. 3313</ref>; renumbered § 22, <ref href="/us/pl/106/210/s4/1">Pub. L. 106–210, § 4(1)</ref>, <date date="2000-05-26">May 26, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/322">114 Stat. 322</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
